	(1097,248,'Mac','brian.mcelaney@gmail.com','http://www.mcelaney.com','199.112.55.146','2005-07-25 14:53:26','2005-07-25 19:53:26','The Joint Combat Camera Center at the Pentagon allows for Flickr like tagging with FTP upload.  Not sure how the software works, but I add the meta information in photoshop using the \"file info\" feature... ftp the file... and it draws all the information out and adds it to a database automatically.  It also has a neat feature in that it allows users to create their own albums and tags of your images.  So if I\'m looking for shots of Marines treating POWs with first aid, I can collect my results from several places in one album (they call a photo box), then decide what I need later.  So far as fearing data loss, I\'m bought into the idea of using an external hard drive  for on site backup (I\'m lovin a 500GB Lacie drive right now) and plan to get a tape drive for off site storage when I get home.  I get a free security deposit box with my checking account and plan to drop a tape off every other week or so.  If my house and bank burn to the ground at the same time, I\'ll have bigger issues than losing my photos!',0,'1',0,'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.0; .NET CLR 1.1.4322)','',0),
