	(1380,61,'Angela','peanut1@hiwaay.net','','216.180.78.119','2005-11-17 00:15:28','2005-11-17 05:15:28','My first encounter with these uber-vile creatures was when I was 9.  I could not breathe, move, speak, or swallow.  My mother found me outside in our storage room close to shock.  They covered the walls and the deep freezer!! I was just going out there to the freezer to get a popsicle and that\'s what I found.  I am now 34, newly married (to an entymologist\'s son, naturally) and am as horrified of them as I was at 9.  They bring out something in me that I don\'t understand.  My fear of these beasties is way beyond my comprehension.  They are the devil.  They used to lurk in our basement where they washer/dryer are, you could hear them jumping around when you opened the door.  Before we married I told my husband that I would not live in this house unless they were completely eradicated.  Now the pest control co. comes every other Friday and treat the outside of the house.  That has done away with them (except for the one the size of a small Volkswagen I saw outside last weekend) and I can breathe easy - sort of.  I still do a quick search of all walls, ceilings, and floors before I walk into a room, and forget abt walking anywhere barefoot or without all the lights on.  I was so glad to find this site and hear of others like me.  I thought I was crazy!  They are entirely too aggressive, there is no need for them to jump all at your face and whatnot when you\'re just trying to destroy them!!',0,'1',0,'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; SV1; .NET CLR 1.0.3705; Media Center PC 3.1)','',0),
