	(1485,308,'apples','applestories@gmail.com','http://applestories.blogspot.com','129.177.45.133','2006-02-19 15:23:02','2006-02-19 20:23:02','I think one thing that makes a lot of people pose a question like that is they (we) don\'t know any better. We\'ve all experienced asking someone a question we were in fact stupid to be asking (like we just didn\'t read what the message said or clicked the wrong button), and the person we ask is, for some reason, in a bad mood or is busy. Then we\'ll often get a reply such as \"everybody knows that\", \"how can you not know this\" or \"figure it out for yourself\".\r\n\r\nWhen we\'ve got an answer such as that once or twice we quickly learn it might be better to change the way we ask. Rather than \"what does this mean? how do I do this?\" we say \"I know I\'m supposed to know this because everyone else seems to...\". People who know nothing about computers see \'everybody else\' knows things, and we don\'t know what is easy and what is not - what \'everybody\' knows and what only people like you would know.\r\n\r\n\r\nNow that is said - I don\'t pose questions like that so I can\'t say I know why some people do. I mess around, look everywhere and click all the buttons until it either works itself out or blows up in my face.',0,'1',0,'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.7.8) Gecko/20050511 Firefox/1.0.4','',0),
