	(122,0,'rss_867bd5c64f85878d03a060509cd2f92c','Y',1,'O:9:\"MagpieRSS\":19:{s:6:\"parser\";i:0;s:12:\"current_item\";a:0:{}s:5:\"items\";a:50:{i:0;a:7:{s:5:\"title\";s:33:\"Donncha: WP-Cache 2.0.20 released\";s:4:\"guid\";s:52:\"http://ocaoimh.ie/2006/12/31/wp-cache-2020-released/\";s:4:\"link\";s:52:\"http://ocaoimh.ie/2006/12/31/wp-cache-2020-released/\";s:11:\"description\";s:646:\"<p>I wouldn&#8217;t normally mention a minor release of a plugin but the <a href=\"http://mnm.uib.es/gallir/?p=930\">new version</a> of WP Cache 2 incorporates (among other fixes) my <a href=\"http://ocaoimh.ie/2006/12/05/caching-wordpress-with-wp-cache-in-a-spam-filled-world\">patch</a> that stops the cache being deleted when a spam comment is made.</p>\n<p>If you run a busy site, then it&#8217;s definitely worth downloading and upgrading!</p>\n<a href=\"http://ocaoimh.ie/tag/irishblogs/\" rel=\"tag\">irishblogs</a>, <a href=\"http://ocaoimh.ie/tag/wordpress/\" rel=\"tag\">WordPress</a>, <a href=\"http://ocaoimh.ie/tag/wp-cache/\" rel=\"tag\">WP Cache</a>\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Sun, 31 Dec 2006 17:40:28 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:7:\"Donncha\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:646:\"<p>I wouldn&#8217;t normally mention a minor release of a plugin but the <a href=\"http://mnm.uib.es/gallir/?p=930\">new version</a> of WP Cache 2 incorporates (among other fixes) my <a href=\"http://ocaoimh.ie/2006/12/05/caching-wordpress-with-wp-cache-in-a-spam-filled-world\">patch</a> that stops the cache being deleted when a spam comment is made.</p>\n<p>If you run a busy site, then it&#8217;s definitely worth downloading and upgrading!</p>\n<a href=\"http://ocaoimh.ie/tag/irishblogs/\" rel=\"tag\">irishblogs</a>, <a href=\"http://ocaoimh.ie/tag/wordpress/\" rel=\"tag\">WordPress</a>, <a href=\"http://ocaoimh.ie/tag/wp-cache/\" rel=\"tag\">WP Cache</a>\";}i:1;a:7:{s:5:\"title\";s:48:\"Weblog Tools Collection: WP Theme: The gathering\";s:4:\"guid\";s:76:\"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2006/12/31/wp-theme-the-gathering/\";s:4:\"link\";s:70:\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~3/68901325/\";s:11:\"description\";s:176:\"<p><a href=\"http://griffinopolis.com/blog/the-gathering-wordpress-theme/\">WP Theme: The gathering</a> Two column, clean, concise, modern, widget ready theme for Wordpress.\n</p>\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Sun, 31 Dec 2006 15:57:04 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:4:\"Mark\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:176:\"<p><a href=\"http://griffinopolis.com/blog/the-gathering-wordpress-theme/\">WP Theme: The gathering</a> Two column, clean, concise, modern, widget ready theme for Wordpress.\n</p>\";}i:2;a:7:{s:5:\"title\";s:64:\"WordPress Podcast: Episode 16: Year-end review of survey results\";s:4:\"guid\";s:61:\"http://wp-community.org/2006/12/31/episode-16-survey-results/\";s:4:\"link\";s:61:\"http://wp-community.org/2006/12/31/episode-16-survey-results/\";s:11:\"description\";s:3014:\"<p>For the die-hard listeners only, this episode clocks in at over an hour, where David and I go through many of the comments, both good and bad, given during our <a href=\"http://wordpresspodcast.org/survey\">listener survey</a>.</p>\n<table width=\"100%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"4\" cellpadding=\"4\">\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">03:51</td>\n<td valign=\"top\">What do you enjoy about the WordPress Podcast?</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The <em><a href=\"http://noidlefrets.blogspot.com/\">No Idle Frets</a></em> jazz guitar podcast</li>\n<li>The <a href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/IRC\">#wordpress</a> IRC channel</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.skype.com/\">Skype</a> with <a href=\"http://www.pamela-systems.com/\">Pamela</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://grammar.qdnow.com/\">Grammar Girl&#8217;s Quick and Dirty Tips for Better Writing</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.pwdmag.co.uk/\">Practical Web Design</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.markkleinhaut.com/\">Mark Kleinhaut</a></li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\">23:05</td>\n<td valign=\"top\"