	(7,1,'2004-10-29 16:17:31','2004-10-29 22:17:31','<p>Here I am again.  After months of nothing I have grown tired of not having a blog. I went through about a thousand different new website names and even more scenerios for what the site should be.  I have built at least ten different blog scripts, okay half way built, and thrown them out.  In the end I decided to use <a href=\"http://wordpress.org/\">wordpress</a>.  Its a good application and its easy to modify once you get the hang of how it operates. </p>\r\n<p>The style sheeting isn\'t done yet and I will probably be finishing it within the week.  I haven\'t done the about page and I haven\'t done the contact page but I have things to write about and the links are piling up.  I will also be posting some of the old content from timmyfury.com here eventually.  Slowly but surely.</p>','The New Blog',0,'',NULL,NULL,'publish','closed','closed','','new-blog','','','2004-10-31 07:05:25','2004-10-31 13:05:25','',0,'http://veryraw.com/history/2004/10/new-blog/',0,'','',10),
	(99,1,'2003-05-26 00:00:32','2003-05-26 05:00:32','\"The french hate us because we saved them from the Germans and they were looking forward to shnitzel.\"','My father on the French',0,'',NULL,NULL,'publish','closed','closed','','father-on-french','','','2006-02-15 09:45:08','2006-02-15 14:45:08','',0,'http://veryraw.com/history/2005/03/99/',0,'','',3),
	(100,1,'2003-06-18 00:00:43','2003-06-18 05:00:43','<img src=\"http://veryraw.com/images/large/1stgradecowboy.jpg\" alt=\"an early illustration\" />\r\n\r\nFunny thing about the picture above is that my affinity for depicting myself in blues and reds hasn\'t changed.  What else hasn\'t changed is my bizarre and somewhat crude drawing style.  I have more of my first grade drawings and you will see in a few days that my sense of humor then was as outlandish as it is now.  Anyway.  Mark says that I am a prophet.  He thinks the ghost behind me is a glum sars cloud.  It would be glum because of how inaffective it is as a killer.  So the prophecy would be \'when I start dressing like a cowboy, an insignificant disease will sweep the land and kill very few.\'  Being that I wear a big texas belt buckle, own several cowboy hats and ride a horse to work everyday.\r\n\r\nWe are doing probabilities in class. We were studying dice and the probabilities of them and Mr. Maruca says, \"...you can\'t roll higher then a 6, we aren\'t playing dungeons and dragons.\" I could almost hear the record scratch.','I wanna be a cowboy!',0,'',NULL,NULL,'publish','closed','closed','','i-wanna-be-a-cowboy','','','2005-03-14 23:11:21','2005-03-15 04:11:21','',0,'http://veryraw.com/history/2005/03/i-wanna-be-a-cowboy/',0,'','',0),
	(10,1,'2004-11-01 08:02:31','2004-11-01 14:02:31','<p>While on my three month hiatus from blogging I purchase myself a bright shiny new <a href=\"http://www.apple.com/ipod/\">40GB iPod</a>. The investment made me a little squeamish due to the $400 investment.  I himmed and hawed for months about the purchase but after selling my 1964 Buick Skylark, I had the money and though, â€œWhy the hell not.â€  So here I am with an iPod.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I had the iPod engraved.  The back says, â€œThe Library of Alexandria, Operation Jail Time.â€  The source of this name is two fold.  The first part is what <a href=\"http://iam.thecolossus.net/\">Mark</a> and I have named our effort to archive all of our mp3â€™s.  The project is named after <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Library_of_Alexandria\">the Royal Library of Alexandria</a> which held all of the secrets of the ancient world but was lost long ago in barbarian raids.  This name has two meanings.  The first is that it is an amazing collection of music, primarily electronic, and the second is that eventually, we are sure, that the barbarians of the <acronym title=\"Recording Industry Association of America\">RIAA</acronym> will get a hold of us and burn our library to the ground like the Huns they are.  Iâ€™ll write about the collection sometime in the future but this entry is dedicated to the iPod. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The second part of the name plays into the idea that someday the <acronym title=\"Recording Industry Association of America\">RIAA</acronym> will find us and we will spend the rest of our lives paying off the fines that they bestow upon us.  â€œOperation Jail Time,â€ its funny, I\'m going to jail, laugh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As of this morning there are exactly 5500 songs on my iPod (Johnny Rebel free).  When I purchased the iPod I was listening to nothing but <acronym title=\"Natianl Public Radio\">NPR</acronym>.  The rest of the radio had become a vapid wasteland of trash.  I couldnâ€™t stand the incessant yammering about things I didnâ€™t care about.  The problem with listening to <acronym title=\"Natianl Public Radio\">NPR</acronym> was that I was also suffering from a mean case of outrage burnout.  This is the what happens when you are so tired of being pissed off about the status of the world that you cease to care.  Needless to say, I was tiring of <acronym title=\"Natianl Public Radio\">NPR</acronym> too.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The iPod turned my life around.  Really.  After I purchased it I didnâ€™t mind the drive to and from work everyday.  Armed with music that fit with every mood I am always equipped for the drive ahead.  With the drive to and from becoming more pleasant, I was in a better mood when I got to work and performed better there.  This has happened in almost every aspect of my life.  Everything I do is more pleasant because I have the music to match the mood.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Although I was originally very apprehensive about spending as much money as I did on the iPod, I am glad that I did.  Now I realize that its probably the best investment I have ever made.  \r\n</p>','How iPod changed my life.',0,'',NULL,NULL,'publish','closed','closed','','ipod-changed-my-life','','','2004-11-04 23:10:21','2004-11-05 04:10:21','',0,'http://veryraw.com/history/2004/11/ipod-changed-my-life/',0,'','',1),
	(11,1,'2004-11-01 15:35:06','2004-11-01 20:35:06','You may think that wearing woman\'s deodarant would make you feel more feminine.  It doesn\'t.  But is sure doesn\'t make you feel like more of a man.','Manhood in question',0,'',NULL,NULL,'publish','closed','','','manhood-in-question','','','2004-11-01 15:35:06','2004-11-01 20:35:06','',0,'http://veryraw.com/history/2004/11/manhood-in-question/',0,'','',4),
	(12,1,'2004-11-02 00:48:58','2004-11-02 05:48:58','<p>So you go into a fancy restaurant and you order your favorite dish. A few minutes later the waiter brings you two bedpans. He says to you, \"This one\'s a stool sample from a dysentary sufferer.  This one\'s from a cholera sufferer. You can have either one.\"</p>\r\n<p>Now you think to yourself, \"this isn\'t what I wanted!\" But you choose anyway</p>\r\n<p>Happy Voting Day! Now get out there and vote as if all your fucking civil liberties depend on it, cause they do.</p>','Vote for your favorite turd',0,'',NULL,NULL,'publish','closed','closed','','election-day-2004','','','2004-11-04 06:24:49','2004-11-04 11:24:49','',0,'http://veryraw.com/history/2004/11/election-day-2004/',0,'','',1),
