	(176,1,'2004-01-21 00:00:57','2004-01-21 05:00:57','<p>So here I am... again. It\'s Wednesday and I think I am going to do my updates every Wednesday. Makes it easier for everyone. Classes have started again. Whoopy.  I can smell the excitement. Most of my classes this semester are actually interesting though which is a plus. In addition, I got a promotion at Camp-in this year. I am now a manager. It\'s a scary concept.</p>\r\n<p>Timmyfury.com will soon be returning to full functionality. I am working on that now that I have finished up weirdhead.org. Over the course of the next week things will come back on-line. I switched host companies recently because the old company (which shall remain nameless) couldn\'t support some of the things that I wanted to do. So I have switched to <a href=\"http://www.nomonthlyfees.com/\">NoMonthlyFees.com</a>. They are super good and pretty cheap. Furthermore, unlike Dreamhost which I won\'t even grace with a link, they are running a full functioning version of PHP. All of the old content from before I switched hosts is gone though cause I lost the SQL files that had the information in them. So we are starting fresh. If you didn\'t notice at the bottom of each one of my entries now there is a link to make comments about what I write here and you can also read other peoples comments. This is different from the graffiti board and in my opinion way better cause now when you comment on something I write and people read it it will actually make sense.</p>\r\n<p>For all those who don\'t know, Code is in Qatar. This is his third time in the Middle East. He emailed me once then I reset my email account and deleted the email by accident. So I don\'t have it to put up here. I\'ll ask Crissy and post it in case anyone wants to write him. Brain Mac dropped me a link from <a href=\"http://www.8bm.com/ncm/2003/061103.htm\">a soldier in Iraq</a>. Really funny. Makes me proud to know that the guys who are protecting my freedom are assholes just like me.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.stevenwright.com/index.shtml\">Steven Wright</a> once said,  \"If Jesus loves me, why doesn\'t he ever call.\" I have always though this was really funny. Which is why I should share <a href=\"http://www.cnn.com/2004/TECH/ptech/01/19/offbeat.finland.jesus.reut/index.html\">this article on CNN</a> with you. Apparently in Finland, Jesus didn\'t call either. But he did text message. But now he\'s not allowed to do that anymore. Fucking bureaucrats.</p>\r\n<p>Last piece of bussiness. <a href=\"http://www.mikerowesoft.com/\">MikeRoweSoft.com</a>. Microsoft says take it down and we\'ll give you $10. The kid is from Canada which leads me to believe that they would give him 10 loonies (10 Canadien dollars) which is worth about $7.50 American. Anyway Microsoft says we\'ll give you $10,  he\'s like fuck you give me $10,000. That rules. Power to the people. I suppose they\'ll be going after <a href=\"http://www.mightgrowsoft.com/\">MightGrowSoft.com</a> next.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.cnn.com/2004/TECH/internet/01/21/offbeat.porn.prayer.reut/index.html\">A final thought.</a></p>\r\n','The future of TimmyFury, Code and Jesus',0,'',NULL,NULL,'publish','closed','closed','','the-future-of-timmyfury-code-and-jesus','','','2005-05-13 06:46:18','2005-05-13 11:46:18','',0,'http://veryraw.com/history/2005/05/the-future-of-timmyfury-code-and-jesus/',0,'','',0),
	(177,1,'2004-01-28 00:00:48','2004-01-28 05:00:48','<p>I have worked at a furiously to get <a href=\"http://www.weirdhead.org/\">weirdhead.org</a> up. This is the official release announcement. It\'s super cool and standards compliant. It validates in every possible way (xhtml, css, 508). This is good  because it\'s my goal to get alot of people out there to see this site and I have read relatively extensively that the best form of advertising is a <a href=\"http://www.alistapart.com/articles/seo/\">good   search engine optimization (SEO) campaign</a>. You have to look at the <a href=\"http://www.alistapart.com/articles/urls/\">URL\'s</a> as you cruise around the site. They are terribly clean. I am rather proud of   it. I have spent about a month and it\'s really magnificent. You can even submit   analysis on the pictures. Take a look. It rules. I\'m gonna submit it to GAWDS to use as my in to the <a href=\"http://www.gawds.org/\">Guild of Accesible Web   Designers</a>.</p>\r\n<p>I worked a campin this weekend and I work another one this weekend. Last weekend   I was just shadowing Candy. This weekend will be my first night as manager. It\'s a relatively scary thought if you ask me. Whatever though. For those that don\'t know, Camp-in is a program at the <a href=\"http://www.fi.edu/\">Franklin   Institue Science Museum</a> that lets children sleep at the museum like a camping trip. It\'s really rad. I love doing it. It\'s one of those jobs that you can believe in. Everyone thats working wants to be there. This is my fourth year.   Manager. The sound of it makes me snicker a touch.</p>\r\n<p>I forgot to mention that Michelle is in England right now. She left like 2 days after Trish and I left for Venice. All is well with her. Here\'s a <a href=\"http://www.urbis.org.uk/\">link to her museum</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Last week I mentioned <a href=\"http://www.mightgrowsoft.com/\">MightGrowSoft.com</a>. There is an article on there that is interesting and I don\'t know what the validity   of it is but heres the general jist. \"Bill Gates has recently announced that he has filed an anti-trust lawsuit against the government of the United   States, claiming they use anti-competitive methods to influence other countries\'   governing processes.\" Okay so that wasn\'t a jist it was the abstract of the article directly from the page. I think the site is all made up stuff to   ream Gates but i don\'t know. I give you the abstract because the article isn\'t   much more and if you go there you are forced to listen to an annoying midi rendition   of the Star Spangled Banner. Then again you might really hate yourself and want   to force yourself to be exposed to that sort of crap. If so, heres the link   - <a href=\"http://www.mightgrowsoft.com/news/gatesusa.html\">Bill Versus The   USA</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Wrapping up, I don\'t know if anyone is familiar with the <a href=\"http://www.chick.com/%20\">Chick religious pamphlet series</a>, but if you are<a href=\"http://www.epsilonminus.com/darquedungeon/\">   here\'s a spoof</a>. and last of all here are some classy articles from CNN.com this week.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.cnn.com/2004/US/South/01/22/doodle.dogs.reut/index.html\">Designer mutts cost big bucks</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.cnn.com/2004/US/Northeast/01/23/molasses.flood.ap/index.html%20\">Great   molasses flood remembered</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.cnn.com/2004/WORLD/europe/01/26/pope.breakdancers.ap/index.html\">Papal   blessing for break-dancers</a></li>\r\n</ul>','World Release of Weirdhead.org',0,'',NULL,NULL,'publish','closed','closed','','world-release-of-weirdheadorg','','','2005-05-13 06:48:13','2005-05-13 11:48:13','',0,'http://veryraw.com/history/2005/05/world-release-of-weirdheadorg/',0,'','',0);
