	(332,1,'2006-04-03 17:32:08','2006-04-03 22:32:08','<p class=\"present\"><a href=\"http://flickr.com/photos/thecnote/121816316/\"><img src=\"http://static.flickr.com/37/121816316_44562ad91e_m.jpg\" alt=\"Skulls and stacks of bones\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>Every now and then I catch something on flickr that makes me stop and say wow.  <a href=\"http://flickr.com/photos/thecnote/\">Thecnote</a> has posted a set of images from the <a href=\"http://flickr.com/photos/thecnote/sets/72057594096613716/\">Sedlec Ossuary</a> in the Czech Republic.  As the surrounding cemetary became more popular, the land became full and bodies were exhumed and the bones stacked in this ossuary.  My favorites?  The <a href=\"http://flickr.com/photos/thecnote/121816630/in/set-72057594096613716/\">bone chandelier</a> and the <a href=\"http://flickr.com/photos/thecnote/121816791/in/set-72057594096613716/\">bone garland</a>. <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sedlec_ossuary\">Read more on wikipedia</a>.</p>','A Church of Bone',0,'',NULL,NULL,'publish','closed','closed','','a-church-of-bone','','','2006-04-04 21:12:07','2006-04-05 02:12:07','',0,'http://veryraw.com/history/2006/04/a-church-of-bone/',0,'','',1),
