	(285,1,'2005-11-08 15:23:27','2005-11-08 20:23:27','<p><a href=\"\">5ives</a> is one of my favorite sites.  A few months ago He wrote a list called <a href=\"http://www.5ives.com/archives/2004/08/17/five-favorite-rumors-of-my-childhood/\">Five favorite rumors of my childhood</a>. Here\'s the list...</p>\r\n<blockquote><ul>\r\n<li>Bubble Yum is made from spiders&#8217; eggs</li>\r\n<li>Mikey died from mixing Pop-Rocks and Coke</li>\r\n<li>That one really weird teacher is &#8220;a gay&#8221;</li>\r\n<li>People get beheaded on Space Mountain, literally, every day</li>\r\n<li>One time, Rod Stewart drank a <em>gallon</em> of semen and totally had to have his stomach pumped </li>\r\n</ul></blockquote>\r\n<p>I loved this cause I remember I had a few of these.  This guy must be a bit older than me cause for me it was Lil\' Kim not Rod Stewart.  I knew a girl in elementary school who wouldn\'t eat butterfingers because she thought they were made with crushed glass.  Someone else I know told me that she thought when you whistle, the angels cry.  I also had a friend, Bobby used to just make things up.  Anything he wanted.  We were building a fort once behind this guys house and there was a stack of fences in his back yard.  Bobby convinced us to steal them because he knew that the guy who owned the house was deaf and blind from a fire in his house.</p>\r\n<p>Anyway, Trish and I were talking to a friend of her\'s a few weeks ago and she brought up Midgetville.  For those who don\'t know, Midgetville is a made up town.  When I was little everyone knew someone who had been there but they had never been there themselves.  Small houses.  The midgets would always run out of their houses and throw rocks at your car.  I thought it was in Springfield.  Trish said near Taylor Hospital.  Michelle said it was near the Granite Run Mall.  The details were different for everyone.</p>\r\n<p>Do you remember any irrational fears or bizarre misconceptions from your childhood?  Where was midgetville for you? Do they throw rocks there?</p>','Everyone knows someone who\'s been to Midgetville!',0,'',NULL,NULL,'publish','closed','closed','','everyone-knows-someone-whos-been-to-midgetville','','','2005-11-08 15:23:37','2005-11-08 20:23:37','',0,'http://veryraw.com/history/2005/11/everyone-knows-someone-whos-been-to-midgetville/',0,'','',15),
	(286,1,'2005-11-05 22:05:00','2005-11-06 03:05:00','<p>I signed up with <a href=\"http://www.dreamhost.com\">Dreamhost</a> a bit ago.  I am now in process of switching hosts from liquidweb to dreamhost.  There will be some time between now and when my DNS updates tot he new server and in that time I am going to disable comments across all of my entries.  If you have input, email me at timothycrowe@gmail.com.  Otherwise we should be completely back to normal in 72 hours.</p>\r\n<p><em>Update!</em> The switch seems to have been a success.  At least locally everything is pointing to my new host.  It also seems to be running smoothly.  Way more painless than I thought it would be.</p>','Switching hosts! ',0,'',NULL,NULL,'publish','closed','closed','','switching-hosts','','','2005-11-06 17:12:48','2005-11-06 22:12:48','',0,'http://veryraw.com/history/2005/11/switching-hosts/',0,'','',1),
	(288,1,'2005-12-02 14:35:52','2005-12-02 19:35:52','<p>I often joke about paramedics, calling them Paramedic Commando, as they scream by in a haze of lights and sirens.  They swerve in and out of traffic.  Driving in the wrong direction and through red lights.  Then in a convenience store they walk around like hot shit, listening to there walkie talkies and talking about all kinds of important things like flashlights and badges.  These guys actually serve an important function though so I\'ll accept it.  It takes a lot to gather up someones brains or intestines and rush them to the hospital.  These guys might actually deserve the title of commando, however crazy they may be.</p>\r\n<p>I have forever been amazed at the delusional crossing guards in this area.  They seem to forget that a car can rip their bodies to bits.  They have zero regard and will walk out in front of your car with only a raised stop sign to protect them.  Your stop sign will not protect you!  I call them Crossing Guard Commando.  This was a play on the aformentioned Paramedic Commando.  The other morning Trish and I were driving to work together and a crossing guard walked out in front of me in full camoflage.  Glad to see that my jokes have real world punchlines.</p>','Crossing Guard Commando',0,'',NULL,NULL,'publish','closed','closed','','crossing-guard-commando','','','2005-12-04 12:00:02','2005-12-04 17:00:02','',0,'http://veryraw.com/history/2005/11/crossing-guard-commando/',0,'','',0),
	(289,1,'2005-11-17 15:17:13','2005-11-17 20:17:13','Well it turns out I was right.  Apparently <a href=\"http://veryraw.com/history/2005/01/decaf-jihad/\">there is something seriously wrong with decaf coffee</a>.  <a href=\"http://www.americanheart.org/presenter.jhtml?identifier=3035336\">A study was released at the American Heart Associationâ€™s Scientific Sessions today that states that decaf may raise the risk of heart disease</a>.\r\n<blockquote>Decaffeinated â€” not caffeinated â€” coffee may cause an increase in harmful LDL cholesterol by increasing a specific type of blood fat linked to the metabolic syndrome, hints a new study presented at the American Heart Associationâ€™s Scientific Sessions 2005.</blockquote>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.americanheart.org/presenter.jhtml?identifier=3035301\">Watch the video of the report</a>.\r\n\r\n</p>','I told you there was something wrong with decaf!',0,'',NULL,NULL,'publish','closed','closed','','i-told-you-there-was-something-wrong-with-decaf','','','2006-02-15 09:13:00','2006-02-15 14:13:00','',0,'http://veryraw.com/history/2005/11/i-told-you-their-was-something-wrong-with-decaf/',0,'','',3),
	(290,1,'2005-12-04 12:23:04','2005-12-04 17:23:04','<p>Tomorrow I will be going to <a href=\"http://aneventapart.com/\">An Event Apart</a>, a one day conference about Web Standards.  Two great names in standards will be there.  <a href=\"http://www.meyerweb.com/\">Eric Meyer</a> and <a href=\"http://www.zeldman.com/\">Jeffrey Zeldman</a> are standards celebrities that I have been reading since I got into standards almost three years ago.  I am probably more excited for this event than I should be (I already have my clothes layed out), but this is not only my first web conference, but its at my favorite place on earth, The Franklin Institute, to boot.</p>\r\n<p>I will be blogging from the event elsewhere.  I\'m joining <a href=\"http://www.jefflouella.com/\">Jeff</a> and <a href=\"http://www.jamesmuspratt.com/\">James</a> and a few others on the <a href=\"http://www.phillystandards.org/blog/\">Philadelphia Standards Organization blog</a> alongside the fellows of <a href=\"http://noteworthy.pixelworthy.com/\">Pixelworthy</a> in documenting the events and the learning and the fun.  If you are in to this sort of thing or just love my awesome writing, <a href=\"http://www.phillystandards.org/blog/\">stop over and visit the blog</a> to see what\'s going on.</p>','Blogging on Standards',0,'',NULL,NULL,'publish','closed','closed','','blogging-on-standards','','','2005-12-04 12:42:37','2005-12-04 17:42:37','',0,'http://veryraw.com/history/2005/12/blogging-on-standards/',0,'','',9),
