	(292,1,'2005-12-13 12:18:37','2005-12-13 17:18:37','<p>I knew going into this movie that there was some layer of Christian symbolism to it.  I had heard on NPR that it was the conservative right\'s response to <em>Lord of the Rings</em> and <em>Harry Potter</em>.  Furthermore, I have read <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0060652896/ref=reg_hu-wl_item-added/002-5824911-8092810?%5Fencoding=UTF8&v=glance&n=283155\">The Screwtape Letters</a> by C.S. Lewis and know a little about him;  beside the fact that a significant portion of the books written from 1800 through 1960 has some level of religious symbolism.  That aside, the film <em>The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe</em> had a rediculous amount of religious symbolism. I don\'t even think I can call it symbolism though.  Symbolism is generally subtle.  Its implied not forced.  The imagery in <em>The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe</em> was so obnoxious that it ruined the movie for me.</p>\r\n<p>A few examples for you...</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>the betrayal of Aslan by Edmund</li>\r\n<li>the insuing forgiving of Edmund</li>\r\n<li>Aslan\'s ultimate sacrifice</li>\r\n<li>the rediculous unexplained resurrection that followed</li>\r\n<li>the bizarre appearance of Santa Clause handing out Christmas presents that had nothing to offer to the story what-so-ever.  He magically knew exactly what the three kids would need to win the lame battle at the end.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>My other complaint is the complete lack of realism in the battle.  No blood, no gore? It\'s a battle for god\'s sake.  Give me something. </p>\r\n<p>The cincher was at the end though.  The kids are all grown up in Narnia-time and as they ride into view in the forest Peter looks like the Burger King.</p> \r\n<img src=\"http://veryraw.com/images/bk.jpg\" />','The Jesus, the Witch and the wardrobe.',0,'',NULL,NULL,'publish','closed','closed','','the-jesus-the-witch-and-the-wardrobe','','','2005-12-13 12:18:57','2005-12-13 17:18:57','',0,'http://veryraw.com/history/2005/12/the-jesus-the-witch-and-the-wardrobe/',0,'','',12),
	(293,1,'2005-12-16 10:12:21','2005-12-16 15:12:21','<p>In my first installment of <a href=\"http://veryraw.com/history/2005/06/apartment-hunt-advice/\">apartment hunting advice</a> I only shared my observations from the actual hunt.  That was in June though, before I have actually moved into my current place.  Trish and I did a pretty good job we found a place that we like and we haven\'t had any major problems.  We did however do something right that we had not planned on.  This might be something to keep in mind. </p>\r\n<p>We rented a place on the second floor of a three floor building.  Because we have someone above and below, we only have two exposed sides to our apartment.  We are touched on the other four sides by three apartments and a hallway.  I believe the high for the last two weeks has not gotten much above freezing and we haven\'t turned our heat on yet. We have electric heat in the apartment.  Souring energy costs are all the rage on the news this winter and I hear people complaining about really high bills because of heat.  We wouldn\'t know though.  There are nights that I have to put on shorts because our apartment is so warm.</p>\r\n<p>My point here is, no matter where your apartment is in the summer, you are going to use your air conditioner.  But if you can choose an apartment in the center of a building, you\'ll  save a significant amount of money in the winter.</p>','More apartment hunting advice: location, location, location.',0,'',NULL,NULL,'publish','closed','closed','','more-apartment-hunting-advice-location-location-location','','','2005-12-16 10:13:49','2005-12-16 15:13:49','',0,'http://veryraw.com/history/2005/12/more-apartment-hunting-advice-location-location-location/',0,'','',3),
	(294,1,'2005-12-21 14:45:24','2005-12-21 19:45:24','<p>Acronyms, particularly technology related acronyms should be used with great care. Using technology related acronyms have a few possible effects. I\'ve made this useful table for you to tell whether you should use them or not based on the knowledge level of the user and recipient and the effect it has.</p>\r\n<table cellpadding=\"5\" border=\"1\">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td></td>\r\n    <th>User knows the acronym</th>\r\n    <th>User does not know the acronym</th>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <th>Recipient does not know the acronym</th>\r\n    <td>User totally looks like a pretentious asshole. Recipient is not impressed</td>\r\n    <td>User looks like a pretentious asshole. Recipient is not impressed</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <th>Recipient knows the acronym</th>\r\n    <td>Good conversation may ensue. Neither is impress by knowledge of acronyms \r\n      used rather by insight into particular topic</td>\r\n    <td>User looks like a complete moron and a fake to boot.</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>I feel similarly about acronyms as I do about the terms <a href=\"http://veryraw.com/history/2005/05/information-superhighway/\">information superhighway and computer guy</a>. If you don\'t know what they mean, they aren\'t for you to use.  As you can see by my handy chart above, in no case are acronyms impressive.  The only person that has ever been impressed with acronyms is your mother and thats not because it makes you look smart.  Your mother was also proud when you started going poopee in the potty.</p>','Acronyms may not be for you.',0,'',NULL,NULL,'publish','closed','closed','','acronyms-may-not-be-for-you','','','2005-12-21 14:51:52','2005-12-21 19:51:52','',0,'http://veryraw.com/history/2005/12/acronyms-may-not-be-for-you/',0,'','',7),
	(296,1,'2005-12-29 00:39:36','2005-12-29 05:39:36','<p>This year was my fourth Christmas with Trish. The first year we were together I bought Trish a gift certificate for sky diving.  She bought me something equally exciting.  The gifts became increasingly outlandish and wild over the course of the next two and a half years.  Nights in fancy hotels, tickets for shows, hot air balloon rides and weekends away were sprinkled in the ranks of gifts.</p>\r\n<p>This was the first Christmas after moving in together.  We laughed the other day after opening each others gifts about how practical the presents have become.  I gave Trish books and movies and a coat rack.  She gave me socks and underwear and a paper shredder.  There was an assortment of other gifts but the overarching trend was practicality.</p>\r\n<p>I have been trying to amass a list of signs that you know you are getting old.  I think that this goes down on the list. Here is wear I stand.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>You get angry at a pot roast for not cooking properly.</li>\r\n<li>You start carrying savings club cards on your keys.</li>\r\n<li>A paper shredder for christmas gets you excited like toys did when you were younger.</li>\r\n</ul>','Inevitable practicality of gifts',0,'',NULL,NULL,'publish','closed','closed','','inevitable-practicality-of-gifts','','','2005-12-29 00:40:26','2005-12-29 05:40:26','',0,'http://veryraw.com/history/2005/12/inevitable-practicality-of-gifts/',0,'','',5),
	(297,1,'2006-01-10 23:40:01','2006-01-11 04:40:01','<img src=\"http://veryraw.com/images/partyPlane.jpg\" alt=\"Screenshot of the moment that Party Plane turns on you\" style=\"float: right;margin: 10px;\" />\r\n<p>Back in the days of the dial-up, I downloaded a song by DJ Alligator Project called \"Party Plane\".  I sent it to <a href=\"http://iam.thecolossus.net\">Mark</a>, the co-creator of the bunny film.  It took him about 2 hours to download. When he listened to it he called me, said \"fuck you\", hung up and didn\'t speak to me for three days.  I\'ve posted it on my site.  You can go <a href=\"http://veryraw.com/files/the_party_plane.mp3\">download it</a> too. It\'s the worst song ever. You\'ll understand why it would be so infuriating to wait 2 hours to here this monstrosity.  Over the years since (this was back before napster when I used mIRC to download music) there have been many things of equivelant attacks.</p>\r\n<p>If you have known <a href=\"http://iam.thecolossus.net\">Mark</a> or myself for any amount of time, you have been \"Party Planed\".  In recent years party plane has turned into being goatse\'d.  Everyone I know has been goatse\'d in every way possible.  We hide them in browser bugs, redirect each other\'s websites, hide them in downloads; you name it.  Mark and I have done it.</p>\r\n<p>I can\'t remember all the ways I have goatse\'d someone.  I saw on <a href=\"http://www.boingboing.net/2006/01/10/flickr_set_of_people.html\">boing boing</a> that there is a <a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/groups/firstgoatse/\">flickr group for pictures of people seeing goatse for the first time</a>.  I need to join the group and start hitting people with the goat.  So if you have been goatse\'d by either myself or <a href=\"http://iam.thecolossus.net\">Mark</a>, comment below.  Tell me about your goatse horror stories.  </p>','Get on the Party Plane',0,'',NULL,NULL,'publish','closed','closed','','get-on-the-party-plane','','','2006-01-10 23:41:48','2006-01