	(357,1,'2006-08-23 08:14:05','2006-08-23 13:14:05','Those who know me know that <a href=\"http://veryraw.com/history/2005/07/nerd-live-here/\">I am a big fan of history and the History Channel</a>.  However, <a href=\"http://iam.thecolossus.net/\">Mark</a> sent me a video yesterday that early made me choke on my <a href=\"http://veryraw.com/history/2006/08/struggling-with-my-inner-nerd/#comment-1869\">historical fiction</a>.  This song, about George Washington is what history education should be.  My favorite line is \"... Got a pocket full of horses, fucked the shit out of bears...\".  Classic.  Go watch it. <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pc9y5ayeeb4\">George Washington</a>.','Washington, Washington, Six foot eight, weighs a fucking ton.',0,'',NULL,NULL,'publish','closed','closed','','washington-washington-six-foot-eight-weighs-a-fucking-ton','','','2006-08-23 08:14:05','2006-08-23 13:14:05','',0,'http://veryraw.com/history/2006/08/washington-washington-six-foot-eight-weighs-a-fucking-ton/',0,'','',2),
	(358,1,'2006-09-06 14:20:24','2006-09-06 19:20:24','I\'ve mentioned it here before, but I am totally addicted to books.  When Trish and I moved recently (more on that later), she said she was going to pack up my books and I almost swallowed my tongue.  <a href=\"http://thenonist.com/index.php/thenonist/permalink/hot_library_smut/\">Hot Library Smut</a> mentions this book, <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Libraries-Umberto-Eco/dp/0500543143/\">Libraries</a>, which is basically just a book of book porn.  Its an awesome combination of books and architecture.\r\n<p><img id=\"image359\" src=\"http://veryraw.com/wp-content/uploads/2006/09/RIJKMUSEUM-AMSTERDAM.jpg\" alt=\"RIJKMUSEUM AMSTERDAM\" /></p>','Addicted to books',0,'',NULL,NULL,'publish','closed','closed','','addicted-to-books','','','2006-09-06 14:20:24','2006-09-06 19:20:24','',0,'http://veryraw.com/history/2006/09/addicted-to-books/',0,'','',4),
	(360,1,'2006-09-10 21:54:57','2006-09-11 02:54:57','<p>Saturday, Brian, Brad and I tore down my shed.  Brian and I had spent an entire day gutting this shed.  It had pretty elaborate shelving, it was fully paneled, insulated (that was fun) and had electricity run to it.  We didn\'t know how we should take the roof off.  Brian and I were planning on getting some ladders and taking the roof off 10 feet up.  Leave it to my brother to find a quicker more destructive way to do it.  <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jpV4E7QNtt8&eurl=http%3A%2F%2Fveryraw%2Ecom%2F\">Watch and enjoy</a>.</p>\r\n<object width=\"425\" height=\"350\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/jpV4E7QNtt8\"></param><embed src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/jpV4E7QNtt8\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" width=\"450\" height=\"350\"></embed></object>','Demolition of a shed',0,'',NULL,NULL,'publish','closed','closed','','demolition-of-a-shed','','','2006-09-11 14:19:48','2006-09-11 19:19:48','',0,'http://veryraw.com/history/2006/09/demolition-of-a-shed/',0,'','',0),
	(361,1,'2006-09-13 19:27:00','2006-09-14 00:27:00','<p>Most everyone who reads my site already knows, but I am officially a homeowner.  Actually Trish and I have been an official homeowners for the last three weeks.  I seem to have mastered the <a href=\"http://veryraw.com/history/2006/09/demolition-of-a-shed/\">demolition</a> part of home repair, but tonight I performed my first successful home repair that didn\'t involve brute force (I also installed my washer and dryer on the day we moved in too but that doesn\'t count cause I had help).  I realigned the deadbolt on the front door so it was easier to lock and unlock.  Now we can  use all three of our doors.  I think this means I am officially handy.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/timmyfury/173788831/\" title=\"Photo Sharing\"><img src=\"http://static.flickr.com/72/173788831_00e190e160.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"375\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>','Settle down',0,'',NULL,NULL,'publish','closed','closed','','settle-down','','','2006-09-14 09:17:14','2006-09-14 14:17:14','',0,'http://veryraw.com/history/2006/09/settle-down/',0,'','',0),
	(362,1,'2006-09-17 07:57:24','2006-09-17 12:57:24','<p style=\"float: right; margin: 0 0 5px 10px;\"><a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/timmyfury/28099400/\" title=\"Photo Sharing\"><img src=\"http://static.flickr.com/23/28099400_431fb8f221_m.jpg\" width=\"240\" height=\"180\" alt=\"Plane\'s goin\' down.  Everybody stay calm!\" /></a>\r\n</p><p>A few years ago in St. Thomas, <a href=\"http://veryraw.com/history/2004/07/parasailing-retard/\">I nearly fell out of my harness when I was parasailing</a>.  Trish nearly died laughing while we were up in the air as I screamed that I was going to fall.  The other day I saw this video of <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xSGJKYuLkNk\">a kid nearly falling out of his harness on a ride</a>.  I shared it with Trish and she said this is what I sounded like as I was clinging to my life 600 feet in the air.</p>','Screaming like the plane\'s going down.',0,'',NULL,NULL,'publish','closed','closed','','screaming-like-the-planes-going-down','','','2006-09-17 07:58:29','2006-09-17 12:58:29','',0,'http://veryraw.com/history/2006/09/screaming-like-the-planes-going-down/',0,'','',1),
	(363,1,'1970-01-01 00:00:00','1970-01-01 00:00:00','<p>As you know, we moved out of our apartment last month and into our new house.  Our apartment was through Media Real Estate.  We received our security deposit check back this evening in the mail and were surprised at the amount of money they took out of the security deposit.  Even more surprising was the itemized list and the values attached to the items on the list.</p>\r\n<p>The list was as follows:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Refrigerator cleaning?  Kitchen floor cleaning?  Bathroom cleaning?  What a total crock of shit.  And don\'t even get me started on the professional carpet cleaning.</p>','Media Real Estate is a dogshit dildo.',0,'',NULL,NULL,'draft','closed','closed','','','','','2006-09-27 18:06:15','2006-09-27 23:06:15','',0,'http://veryraw.com/?p=363',0,'','',0),
	(364,1,'2006-10-07 15:08:51','2006-10-07 20:08:51','About a month ago along with 5 other beer enthusiasts I launched <a href=\"http://mugwarrior.com\">Mug Warrior</a>.  Its about beer.  Its about glassware.  Its about the experience.  Its the total package and anything to do with our favorite beverage.  We\'re just getting started but there are some ideas that could turn out to be fun.  Take a look around.  <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/MugWarrior>Subscribe to the feed</a>.  Enjoy.','Me Thirsty.  Me want beer!',0,'',NULL,NULL,'publish','closed','closed','','me-thirsty-me-want-beer','','','2006-10-07 15:10:18','2006-10-07 20:10:18','',0,'http://veryraw.com/history/2006/10/me-thirsty-me-want-beer/',0,'','',0),
	(365,1,'2006-10-29 20:40:43','2006-10-30 01:40:43','As if you thought they didn\'t get more important than the 2004 presidential elections, this year comes out of nowhere and slaps you in the face like you\'re an enemy combatant in questioning in Guantanamo Bay.  With a third of the Senators and every single Congressmen up for re-election, this election year is the equivalent to the 2000 and 2004 election years combined for the legislative branch.  At heart I am a social progressive, I\'m a fiscal conservative, you might call me a true democrat.  Lower taxes and increase social programs (as if).  I would love to be able to say that I wanted democrats to take control of Congress, but I can\'t! There is so much fluff and bullshit on both sides of the government that I throw up a little bit in my mouth every time I think about that fateful Tuesday in November when at least 2 members of Congress expect me to hand them another couple of years to tool around with my country.  There are more scandels than I care to mention.  Worst of all though is that Congress has been handing President Bush power that is unrivaled by the government of <em>1984</em>.  After the FBI recently invaded the home of a man who created a program to <a href=\"http://www.boingboing.net/2006/10/29/ceci_nest_pas_un_fak.html\">make fake boarding passes</a>.  After a bill is signed giving Goerge Bush the authority to declare Marshall Law on our own people.  After Congress has allowed George Bush to declare anyone <a href=\"http://mobones.mcelaney.com/?p=27\">a criminal without telling them why</a>.  It\'s time to transition the government to a different group of people.  \r\n\r\nThe current government isn\'t doing what the American people need them to do.  We need to vote against every single incumbent regardless of what they are currently doing.  My barber has a great opinion on polititians.  After the promises, the first year in office is for the people.  The rest of them are for themselves.  \r\n\r\nI\'m voting Casey, I\'m voting Sestak.  Regardless of policy.  I may not agree with everything that the challengers are saying, but for fucksake we couldn\'t do any worse than we are doing now.  ','Give me more incumbents to vote against!',0,'',NULL,NULL,'publish','closed','closed','','give-me-more-incumbents-to-vote-against','','','2006-10-29 20:40:43','2006-10-30 01:40:43','',0,'http://veryraw.com/history/2006/10/give-me-more-incumbents-to-vote-against/',0,'','',2),
	(366,1,'2006-11-14 19:18:50','2006-11-15 00:18:50','One of my favorite sayings is, \"You can\'t polish a turd.\"  It insinuates that a bad idea is a bad idea, and a fuck up is a fuck up no matter what you do.  However, recently it came to my attention that this ancient Persian proverb may not be as accurate as I first thought.  \r\n\r\nIts called <a href=\"http://www.dorodango.com/about.html\">hikaru dorodango</a>.  The description from the site reads, \"Hikaru dorodango are balls of mud, molded by hand into perfect spheres, dried, and polished to an unbelievable luster. The process is simple, but the result makes it seem like alchemy.\" It\'s an amazing transformation from dirt and water to a beautiful sphere of wonder. Just take a look at the <a href=\"http://www.dorodango.com/gallery.html\">gallery</a>.  It includes several awesome transformations from around New Mexico.\r\n\r\nThis gets me thinking.  Perhaps if you could do this with mud, couldn\'t you also do it with shit?  If so, it means the death of one of my favorite sayings. Good bye old friend, hello polished turd collection.','Beautiful polished spheres',0,'',NULL,NULL,'publish','closed','closed','','beautiful-polished-spheres','','','2006-11-14 19:18:50','2006-11-15 00:18:50','',0,'http://veryraw.com/history/2006/11/beautiful-polished-spheres/',0,'','',2),
	(368,1,'2006-11-16 09:22:22','2006-11-16 14:22:22','<p style=\"float: right; padding: 0 0 5px 10px;\"><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2006/11/sacagawea.jpg\" /></p>\r\n<p>I\'ve written in the past about my <a href=\"http://veryraw.com/history/2005/04/eisenhower-dollars/\">fondness of the dollar coin</a>.  I find them far more convenient than paper dollars and just think that there is something aesthetically pleasing about the way they feel in your hand and pocket.  Dan Platt once said that the reason I like them is that it brings me back to my <acronym title=\"Dungeons and Dragons\">D&D</acronym> days, but in real life.  He said that I just liked having a pocket full of copper, silver and gold so I could pretend I was going to the tavern to drink a stein of mead before I wen adventuring to clobber a band of bugbears.</p>\r\n<p style=\"float: right; padding: 0 0 5px 10px;\"><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2006/11/twodollarbill.jpg\" /></p>\r\n<p>However, I enjoy all sort of off-the-norm denominations of money.  particularly the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_two-dollar_bill\">two dollar bill</a>.  However, I recently read an article on the Washington Post that has made me quite happy.  There has been a <a href=\"http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/11/08/AR2006110801990.html\">resurgence in the popularity of one of my favorite denominations</a>.  Strip clubs and bars are embracing the bill as a way to increase tipping, but there are other areas that are picking them up as well.  The article makes a good observation however about the two dollar bill.  In the article, Peter Morici, professor at the Robert H. Smith School of Business at the University of Maryland, is quoted as saying \"In order to have a successful $2 bill, you have to have a successful $1 coin.\"  This leads back to my original love for the dollar coin.  I was rather happy to find this little bit of legislation, <a href=\"http://usmint.gov/mint_programs/$1coin/index.cfm\">The Presidential $1 Coin Act of 2005</a>.  They are going to be minting dollar coins in honor of each of the presidents.  Four new coins a year.  Looks like there will be more dollar coins soon, so more two dollar bills.  Looks like I\'m gonna have to find me a <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bag_of_holding\">bag of holding</a> to carry all this treasure around.</p>','A pocket of copper, silver and gold pieces',0,'',NULL,NULL,'publish','closed','closed','','a-pocket-of-copper-silver-and-gold-pieces','','','2006-11-16 15:57:38','2006-11-16 20:57:38','',0,'http://veryraw.com/history/2006/11/a-pocket-of-copper-silver-and-gold-pieces/',0,'','',4),
	(371,1,'2006-11-20 10:27:43','2006-11-20 15:27:43','<p>The other day at the grocery store I found a winning lottery ticket worth $10.  It\'s like finding a $10 bill on the ground that you need to work for.  I\'m okay with that though.  So on my way into work this morning, I stopped at a newspaper stand near the <a href=\"http://www.usc.edu/schools/annenberg/asc/projects/comm544/library/images/806.html\">clothespin</a>.  I gave the Indian fellow behind the counter my ticket to cash and he proceeded to mock me.</p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>Ooooooh, High Roller. Who has the big bucks now.  Ten big American dollars!  You want this in cash or you want me to make out a check for you?</p><p>\r\n</p></blockquote>\r\n','Mocked for a $10 lottery ticket.',0,'',NULL,NULL,'publish','closed','closed','','mocked-for-a-10-lottery-ticket','','','2006-11-20 10:27:43','2006-11-20 15:27:43','',0,'http://veryraw.com/history/2006/11/mocked-for-a-10-lottery-ticket/',0,'','',0),
